# 7. 試験の結果は……

Rui: Mizuki and Tsukasa should be out soon...
Toya: Yes... Though, Akito and Shiraishi have two subjects, so they'll be longer...
Mizuki: *Sigh* I'm so tired...
Mizuki: Wait, have you two been waiting for us?
Rui: Welcome back, Mizuki. How did it go?
Mizuki: I passed with flying colors, of course!
Toya: Did you? That's good.
Mizuki: Thanks! Tsukasa should be back soon too, don't you think?
Toya: Yes. I believe so...
Tsukasa: Oh, have I kept you three waiting?
Rui: Tsukasa, how did it... No, I don't need to ask.
Tsukasa: Exactly! I passed, of course!
Toya: Congratulations, Tsukasa!
Mizuki: Woohoo! So you'll still be in the year above me next year!
Tsukasa: Uh, yes... Now that you mention it, it's frightening to think about what could have been. That was a close shave...
Tsukasa: Once again... Thank you, Rui. Thanks to you, I'll be able to go into third year.
Rui: Hehe, there's no need to thank me. I want us to be third-years together.
Mizuki: So this just leaves Li'l Bro and An, right?
Tsukasa: Yes. Come on you two, you can do it!
Toya: Akito... Shiraishi...
Mizuki: Hahaha... Don't fret about them. I caught a glimpse of them when I left the classroom, and they were both concentrating super hard.
Toya: Really...? If you say so...
???: It's finally over...
???: I'm so tired...
Toya: Akito, Shiraishi...!
Akito: Sorry to keep you guys waiting.
Toya: We don't mind... But, how did it go?
Akito: I...
Akito: Well, I messed up some questions, but it was alright in the end.
Toya: It was?!
Tsukasa: Good job, Akito!
Akito: Uh... Sure. Thank you.
Mizuki: And An? What about you?
An: I...
An: I passed!
An: Not just that, look...! I got a perfect score in classics!
Mizuki: Seriously?! That's amazing!
An: Yeah! The teacher told me I did a really good job!
Akito: Whoa, not bad.
Toya: You earned this, Shiraishi.
Rui: Congratulations, Shiraishi.
An: Thank you! All of you, from the bottom of my heart.
Mizuki: So everyone passed. Yay!
Akito: Yeah. Though, apparently...
Akito: We could've taken this test as many times as it took.
An: Wait, what do you mean?! We had more than one chance?
Akito: Yeah. This one guy failed, but the teacher just sent him back to his desk to try again.
An: Are you serious?! So, we didn't actually need to study that hard for it?
Akito: Well, if we didn't study a little bit, we'd never get some questions right no matter how many times we tried.
Rui: Exactly. Also, I imagine the teacher purposefully kept quiet about that part.
Rui: If students knew that they had unlimited attempts, at least some of them would slack off.
An: Oh... That makes sense.
An: But... I think I preferred it this way.
Mizuki: You did?
An: Hmm... I was thinking during the test.
An: About how nice it's been studying with you guys this past week.
Toya: Shiraishi...
An: You guys worked so hard to teach me so much, and I became able to answer questions that I was clueless about at first...
An: I realized how much your support and kindness have kept me afloat.
An: And I realized how glad that makes me feel!
An: Also... I was really pleased to be able to answer the questions. Especially since I can finally read Classical Japanese...
An: I even got to understand what the person writing it was feeling... It was kinda fun.
An: I usually don't like studying since it's so hard, but I realized that it's not all so bad.
Akito: I know what you mean. When I finally solved those math problems that'd given me so much trouble, I had a real sense of accomplishment.
Tsukasa: Yes! I've also come to enjoy physics more than before!
An: I still don't exactly love studying...
An: But I'm really happy I did my best!
Rui: Shiraishi...
An: I have all of you to thank for this. Not just you three for teaching us, but you two for studying so hard alongside me...
An: So, thank you so much!
